<subSubSection id="C32A651DFFE4762B3090FF7ABA525391" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8F3696FFE4762B3090FF7AB8445131" blockId="2.[166,1225,223,1018]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">
In total 95 nests of 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B31FCFF7AB9785091" baseAuthorityName="Dahlbom" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[439,596,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Psenulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFE4762B31FCFF7AB9785091" box="[439,596,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">P. fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were obtained. The diameter of stems with wasp nests varied from 5. 
<quantity id="4CC89B73FFE4762B3107FF65BACD5172" box="[332,481,255,282]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.85" metricValueMax="7.7" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="3.85" valueMax="7.7" valueMin="0.0">0 to 7.7 mm</quantity>
; the number of cells per nest varied from 5 to 31 (mode — 18, average — 16.5). The total number of cells was 1503. Mortality was observed in 97 (6.5 %) cells: in 68 cases at the egg stage, in 29 cases as young larvae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F3696FFE4762B3090FEC5BA6F51F1" blockId="2.[166,1225,223,1018]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">
Other 621 (41.3 %) cells of 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B325EFEFAB99F5111" baseAuthorityName="Dahlbom" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[533,691,351,377]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Psenulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFE4762B325EFEFAB99F5111" box="[533,691,351,377]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">P. fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were occupied or destroyed by different wasp enemies:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F3696FFE4762B3090FE05B89551B1" blockId="2.[166,1225,223,1018]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">
435 — by 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B3104FE05B9FF51D1" authority="Abeille, 1878" authorityName=": Abeille de Perrin" authorityYear="1878" box="[335,723,415,441]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera" genus="Omalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sculpticollis">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFE4762B3104FE05B91A51D1" box="[335,566,415,441]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Omalus sculpticollis</emphasis>
Abeille, 1878
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B32A9FE05B8A651D1" box="[738,906,415,441]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Hymenoptera</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B33DEFE05BF0451D2" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[917,1064,415,442]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chrysididae</taxonomicName>
), though only 
<specimenCount id="9D36FD1FFFE4762B3090FE25BA5451B1" box="[219,376,447,473]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" type="generic">90 specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B31D6FE5AB96951B1" authorityName=": Abeille de Perrin" authorityYear="1878" box="[413,581,447,474]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera" genus="Omalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sculpticollis">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFE4762B31D6FE5AB96951B1" box="[413,581,447,474]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">O. sculpticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found in the nests overall;
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F3696FFE4762B3090FE45BF3A5192" blockId="2.[166,1225,223,1018]" box="[219,1046,479,506]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">
116 — by 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B311AFE45B9915191" authority="Walker, 1839" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1839" box="[337,701,479,505]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Melittobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acasta">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFE4762B311AFE45B9365191" box="[337,538,479,505]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Melittobia acasta</emphasis>
Walker, 1839
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B3287FE45B8585191" box="[716,884,479,505]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Hymenoptera</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B3334FE45BF265192" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1829" box="[895,1034,479,506]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Eulophidae</taxonomicName>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F3696FFE4762B3090FE65B8D55272" blockId="2.[166,1225,223,1018]" box="[219,1017,511,538]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">
38 — by 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B3108FE65B9CA5272" authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[323,742,511,538]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Trichodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apiarius">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFE4762B3108FE65B9355271" box="[323,537,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Trichodes apiarius</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B32BFFE65B8565271" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[756,890,511,537]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B33CDFE65B8C15272" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[902,1005,511,538]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cleridae</taxonomicName>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F3696FFE4762B3090FD85BFE55252" blockId="2.[166,1225,223,1018]" box="[219,1225,543,570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">
32 —by 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B317CFD85B8355252" authority="(Thunberg, 1822)" baseAuthorityName="Thunberg" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[311,793,543,570]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Perithous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="septemcinctorius">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFE4762B317CFD85B97A5251" box="[311,598,543,569]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Perithous septemcinctorius</emphasis>
(Thunberg,1822)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B3368FD85B8EE5251" box="[803,962,543,569]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Hymenoptera</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B3381FD85BF555251" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[970,1145,543,569]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ichneumonidae</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="130B2A13FFE4762B34CFFD85BF975252" box="[1156,1211,543,570]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,195,1722,1742]" captionTargetBox="[234,1181,1178,1703]" captionTargetId="graphics-340@2.[234,1021,1178,1702]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Reproductive success and mortality of Psenulus fuscipennis progeny caused by different enemy species and other affects (in terms of number of cells). Рис. 2. Репродуктивный успех и гибель потомства Psenulus fuscipennis от различных видов врагов и других факторов (в перерасчёте на количество ячеек)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403893/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">fig.2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F3696FFE4762B3090FDA5BAA25292" blockId="2.[166,1225,223,1018]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">
The final results are that 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B326FFDDAB9FF5231" authorityName=": Abeille de Perrin" authorityYear="1878" box="[548,723,575,602]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera" genus="Omalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sculpticollis">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFE4762B326FFDDAB9FF5231" box="[548,723,575,602]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">O. sculpticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the main regulator of 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B3468FDDABFE55231" baseAuthorityName="Dahlbom" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[1059,1225,575,601]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Psenulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFE4762B3468FDDABFE55231" box="[1059,1225,575,601]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">P. fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
abundance. As a consequence, only the 52.2 % of 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B32B9FDFAB8BD5211" baseAuthorityName="Dahlbom" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[754,913,607,633]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Psenulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFE4762B32B9FDFAB8BD5211" box="[754,913,607,633]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">P. fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
emerged from their nests. 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B30EDFDE5BABF52F1" baseAuthorityName="Dahlbom" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[166,403,639,665]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Psenulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFE4762B30EDFDE5BABF52F1" box="[166,403,639,665]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Psenulus fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were at a prepupal or pupal stage during the examination of the nests in the third decade of April. The emergence of imagoes took place about two months later, at the end of June. Consequently, we conclude that this species overwinters as prepupa enclosed in cocoon.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F3696FFE4762B3090FD65BA525391" blockId="2.[166,1225,223,1018]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">
Previously 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B3128FC9AB92B5371" baseAuthorityName="Dahlbom" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[355,519,767,793]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Psenulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFE4762B3128FC9AB92B5371" box="[355,519,767,793]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">P. fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was reported as monovoltine species, at least throughout 
<collectingCountry id="F3277606FFE4762B30EDFC85BBF05351" box="[166,220,799,825]" name="Italy" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Italy</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA14B67FFE4762B30A1FC85BAA25352" author="Bonelli, B." box="[234,398,799,826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" pagination="79 - 88" refId="ref8317" refString="Bonelli, B. Note sul comportamento di nidificazione di Psenulus fuscipennis (Dahlb.), Tachysphex fulvitarsis erythogaster (Costa), Sphex albisectus Lep. e Serv. e Sphex occitanicus Lep. e Serv. (Hymenoptera - Sphecidae) // Boll. Inst. Ent. &quot; G. Grandi &quot; Univ. Bologna. - 1988. - 43. - P. 79 - 88." type="book chapter" year="1988">Bonelli, 1988</bibRefCitation>
). In the present study the 11.1 % of 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B3367FCBAB8E15351" baseAuthorityName="Dahlbom" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[812,973,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Psenulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFE4762B3367FCBAB8E15351" box="[812,973,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">P. fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
emerged in summer, before the removal of the sheaves. In fact, we found 87 cells in 16 nests (the 5.8 % of the cells) with empty cocoons. The cells with abandoned cocoons were the outermost, being constructed last. Only one nest was completely empty — all cells contained abandoned 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFE4762B30EDFC3ABA6153D1" baseAuthorityName="Dahlbom" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[166,333,927,953]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Psenulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFE4762B30EDFC3ABA6153D1" box="[166,333,927,953]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">P. fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cocoons. Apparently a part of the studied population of the crabronid wasp gave rise to the so called “facultative generation”, while the rest of the offsprings was monovoltine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
